		<p>Computer Science & Engineering is an academic program at many universities which comprises scientific and engineering aspects of computing.<BR> <BR>CSE is also a term often used in Europe to translate the name of engineering informatics academic programs.
What does a Computer Science Engineer do?<BR><BR>

 

1. Design and develop software application for different industries<BR>
2. Manages the software, hardware & networks in any industry<BR>
3. Involves in the design and development of the hardware components of PCs & laptops<BR>
4. Develop software for peripheral computing devices such as printers, modems and scanners<BR>
5. Writes code and algorithms for operating systems like Windows, Linux etc.</p><BR>
